132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 328
H.P. 228 House of Representatives, February 3, 2025
An Act Requiring the State to Pay a Retired State Employee's or
Retired Teacher's Premium for Medicare Part B Under Medicare
Advantage
Received by the Clerk of the House on January 30, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Labor pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative SHAGOURY of Hallowell.
Cosponsored by Senator HICKMAN of Kennebec and
Representatives: BECK of South Portland, BRIDGEO of Augusta, DODGE of Belfast,
HASENFUS of Readfield, MONTELL of Gardiner, ROLLINS of Augusta, SKOLD of
Portland.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §285, sub-§7, ¶N is enacted to read:
3 N. Beginning January 1, 2026, the State, through the commission, shall pay 100% of
4 a retiree's Medicare Part B premium under the Medicare Advantage plan identified and
5 offered by the commission and available to the retiree as authorized by the commission
6 if the retiree is not eligible for federally approved Medicaid services.
7 Sec. 2. 20-A MRSA §13451, sub-§6 is enacted to read:
8 6. Payment by State for Medicare Part B under Medicare Advantage. Beginning
9 January 1, 2026, the State shall pay 100% of a retired teacher's Medicare Part B premium
10 under the Medicare Advantage plan administered by the Maine Education Association
11 benefits trust if the retired teacher is not eligible for federally approved Medicaid services.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This bill requires the State to pay 100% of a retired state employee's or retired teacher's
1144 premium for Medicare Part B under the Medicare Advantage plan beginning January 1,
1155 2026.
